01/10/2002
MAR DEL PLATA, Argentina -- The volleyball teams of Bulgaria and Yugoslavia cruised into the second round at the 15th Men's World Championship, held in Argentina. 
Yugoslavia easily ousted Spain and Kazakhstan, and is favoured to beat Japan. 
Bulgaria upset volleyball legend Russia, sweeping them in a 3-0 game. 
Bulgaria also beat Tunisia to advance to the next round. 
(Fédération Inernationale de Volleyball - 01/10/02)
